  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to compare shapes to decide which is larger. Given their prior experiences with length, students may initially use length to reason about what it means for a shape to be larger than another shape. The synthesis should bring out the idea that length alone is not enough to compare two-dimensional shapes. Ideas around how much space the shapes cover should be emphasized. If students disagree about which shape is larger, encourage them to share their reasoning so that the class can consider multiple ideas and come to a resolution together (MP3).</p>
  </paragraphs>


